<h2>How to use iVacuum</h2>

<h3>1. Open the app and review the disclosure</h3>
<p>On first launch, iVacuum explains what it does ; scans your photo
library, enhances files to take up less space, and replaces the originals.
Tick the box and tap Continue to proceed.</p>

<h3>2. Unlock iVacuum</h3>
<p>iVacuum is unlocked with a single one-time purchase. There are no
subscriptions and no recurring charges. If you've purchased before
(including on a previous device), tap <strong>Restore Purchases</strong> to
unlock the app again at no extra cost.</p>

<h3>3. Scan your library</h3>
<p>Tap <strong>Scan My Library</strong>. iVacuum will ask for permission to
access your photos and videos, then check how much space your existing
files are using. This step doesn't change anything yet.</p>

<h3>4. Review your results</h3>
<p>You'll see how many files can be enhanced and roughly how much extra
storage you could get back, before anything happens.</p>

<h3>5. Tap Enhance All</h3>
<p>iVacuum will go through your library and enhance each eligible photo and
video. Keep the app open while this runs ; larger libraries with video may
take a few minutes.</p>

<h3>6. Done</h3>
<p>Once finished, you'll see exactly how much extra storage you got back.
You can scan again any time to check for new files to enhance.</p>

<h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Does iVacuum delete any of my photos or videos?</h3>
  <p>No. iVacuum replaces each original with an enhanced version of the
  same photo or video ; nothing is removed from your library, and no
  content is deleted.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Are my photos and videos uploaded anywhere?</h3>
  <p>No. All scanning and enhancement happens locally on your device.
  Nothing is sent to a server or any third party.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>I paid before but I'm being asked to pay again. What do I do?</h3>
  <p>This usually happens after reinstalling the app or switching devices.
  On the unlock screen, tap <strong>Restore Purchases</strong> ; this
  restores access at no additional cost, as long as you're signed in with
  the same Apple ID used for the original purchase.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Is this a subscription?</h3>
  <p>No. iVacuum uses a single one-time purchase for lifetime access.
  There are no recurring charges.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>Why does iVacuum need access to my photos?</h3>
  <p>Photo library access is required so iVacuum can scan your existing
  files and save enhanced versions back to your library. See our
  <a href="https://adsundae-design.github.io/-ivacuum-privacy/">Privacy
  Policy</a> for full details on what the app does and does not do with
  your data.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
  <h3>The app says nothing can be enhanced. Why?</h3>
  <p>iVacuum skips files that are already small or efficiently compressed,
  since there's little space to gain. If your library is already
  optimized, there may simply be nothing left for it to do.</p>
</div>

